<h1>Section Labels</h1>
<p>
  Real songs have structure: verses, choruses, bridges. Grigson uses
  square-bracket labels — <code>[Verse]</code>, <code>[Chorus]</code>,
  <code>[Bridge]</code> — to divide a chart into named sections.
</p>
<p>
  Sections group bars both visually and semantically. Each section can
  optionally declare its own <code>key:</code>, which is useful for songs that
  modulate between sections (covered in a later lesson). Here both sections
  share the global key of G.
</p>
<p>
  The rendered output keeps the section labels visible, giving performers an
  at-a-glance map of the song's form.
</p>
